    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gymnospermous plants with lineage dating back only to the early Cretaceous; widely considered to be the closest extant relative of the flowering plants. Plants are trees, shrubs, lianes, and stumpy turnip-like plants. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
